Structural Divergence Analysis

Maria Laura Marcos, Julian Echave

Introduction

In this case we studied the snakesToxin family. We used as reference for the ENM the protein with pdb code 1ntx. We simulated 10 mutants of this reference for each protein of the family. The snakesToxin family is of the type small and consists of the following proteins:

##  [1] "2crt"  "2cdx"  "1cdta" "1tgxa" "1kxia" "1tfs"  "1drs"  "1txb" 
##  [9] "2ctx"  "1ntn"  "1lsi"  "2abxa" "2nbta" "1nean" "1nor"  "1cod" 
## [17] "1nxb"  "1fas"  "1kbt"
